    "rich_text_jCLkJQ": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_YGeyXi": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>There isn’t a single name behind Atelier Marinière.<br/>There are people.<br/>People who came from different places,<br/>but see things the same way when the light falls just right.<br/><br/>There’s someone who moves through Paris like it’s home—<br/>not out of nostalgia,<br/>but because some ideas only catch you there.<br/>They follow him through the streets.<br/>He brings them back,<br/>puts them in order with the calm of someone who knows<br/>what’s worth keeping<br/>and what deserves to be let go.<br/><br/>There’s someone who speaks through shapes and colors.<br/>They don’t collect objects.<br/>They surround themselves with things that have lived enough<br/>to stay quiet.<br/>A lamp that feels right.<br/>A belt worn in the exact spot.<br/>A blue box that looks like nothing—<br/>but that’s where everything begins.<br/><br/>There’s someone from Venice,<br/>from a place where you don’t learn a craft—<br/>it’s handed down to you.<br/>They recognise a good yarn at the first touch<br/>and sit at the loom with the steady rhythm<br/>of someone who never forces their hand.<br/><br/>There’s someone who’s lived more lives than they can tell.<br/>You see it in their eyes.<br/>Every image they create<br/>is a piece of the world they didn’t want to lose.<br/><br/>And there’s someone who works between algorithms and intuition,<br/>with the same precision as winding an old mechanical watch—<br/>doing it simply for the pleasure of the gesture.<br/><br/>Around them, a small constellation of friends.<br/>People who don’t need to be persuaded.<br/>People who know how to recognise value when it passes by,<br/>even when it passes in silence.<br/><br/>That’s where our pieces begin.<br/>From carefully chosen yarns,<br/>from hands that know what they’re doing,<br/>from looms that never rush.<br/>We make 99 pieces every three months.<br/>Not to be rare—<br/>but because we have no interest in filling the world<br/>with things no one needs.<br/><br/>Beauty lives in choices, not in how many.<br/>In quiet reassurance, not in applause.<br/>In the eyes of someone who notices,<br/>not in the noise around them.<br/><br/>Making less gives us two luxuries:<br/>the time to do things well,<br/>and the certainty that every piece will find<br/>the person it belongs to.<br/>No stock.<br/>No sales.<br/>No shortcuts.<br/><br/>Most people will think it’s just a striped shirt.<br/>And that’s perfect.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
