        "custom_liquid": "<div class=\"page-width\">\n<p class=\"h1\">There isn’t a single name behind Atelier Marinière.<br>\nThere are people.<br>People who came from different places,<br>but see things the same way when the light falls just right.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nThere’s someone who moves through Paris like it’s home<br>\nnot out of nostalgia,<br>but because some ideas only catch you there.<br>\nThey follow him through the streets.<br>\nHe brings them back,<br>puts them in order with the calm of someone who knows what’s worth keepingand <br>what deserves to be let go.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nThere’s someone who speaks through shapes and colors.<br>They don’t collect objects.<br>They surround themselves with things that have lived enough to stay quiet.<br>A lamp that feels right.<br>A belt worn in the exact spot.<br>A blue box that looks like nothing<br>but that’s where everything begins.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nThere’s someone from Venice,<br>from a place where you don’t learn a craft;<br>it’s handed down to you.<br>They recognise a good yarn at the first touch <br>and sit at the loom with the steady rhythm of someone who never forces their hand.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nThere’s someone who’s lived more lives <br>than they can tell.<br>You see it in their eyes.<br>Every image they create<br>is a piece of the world they didn’t want to lose.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nAnd there’s someone who works between algorithms and intuition,<br>with the same precision as winding an old mechanical watch,<br>doing it simply for the pleasure of the gesture.</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">Around them, a small constellation of friends.<br>People who don’t need to be persuaded.<br>People who know how to recognise value when it passes by, even when it passes in silence.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nThat’s where our pieces begin.<br>From carefully chosen yarns,<br>from hands that know what they’re doing,<br>from looms that never rush.</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">We make 99 pieces every three months.<br>Not to be rare<br>but because we have no interest in filling the world with things no one needs.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nBeauty lives in choices, not in how many.<br>In quiet reassurance, not in applause.<br>In the eyes of someone who notices, not in the noise around them.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nMaking less gives us two luxuries:<br>the time to do things well, and the certainty that every piece will find the person it belongs to.<br>No stock.<br>No sales.<br>No shortcuts.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nMost people will think it’s just a striped shirt.\n</p>\n<p class=\"h1\">\nAnd that’s perfect.</p>\n</a>\n</div>",
