        "heading_Fk3rQt": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "About Us",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_ancTJK": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Atelier Marinière is a project shaped between Paris and Venice, moving naturally between France and Italy.</p><p>It was born from a long relationship with fashion, and from the desire to step away from its noise, speed and excess.</p><p>The brand focuses on a small number of essential pieces, rooted in a precise idea of taste, culture and everyday elegance.</p><p>Working with a limited drop model allows Atelier Marinière to concentrate on what matters: materials, proportions and coherence.</p><p>Each collection is released every three months, following the rhythm of the seasons.<br/><br/>Every drop is produced in 99 pieces only, made in Italy, and available for a defined period of time.</p><p>Once a drop is closed, those pieces are never produced again.</p><p>Atelier Marinière believes in making less, but making it well.</p><p>Colours and volumes respond to the present — often anticipating it — while the quality of the materials and construction is meant to last for years, not just for a season.</p><p>Access is occasional, quantities are finite, and waiting is part of the experience.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
